Barcelona qualified for the semi-finals of the Champions League after a 3-0 second-leg thrashing of Manchester United at the Camp Nou on Tuesday. Lionel Messi scored twice in the first half before Philippe Coutinho added the third to clinch a 4-0 aggregate win. The five-time European champions will face either Liverpool or Porto in the last four in their first appearance at the stage of the competition since 2015.  